    },
    {
      "id": "yAVoPXiLmYRMNxdGUEjJM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 312,
      "y": 593,
      "width": 380.87982177734375,
      "height": 75,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aF",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1100559849,
      "version": 81,
      "versionNonce": 1156447209,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783956923885,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\"MSDN\" - old skool documentation, etc.\n  \"MCT\" - Microsoft Certified Trainers\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\"MSDN\" - old skool documentation, etc.\n  \"MCT\" - Microsoft Certified Trainers\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "o7YL5oE7o1tPSJb5_0NSX",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 318,
      "y": 695,
      "width": 1052.4794921875,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aG",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2084908041,
      "version": 832,
      "versionNonce": 411328105,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1783957479144,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "\"Alt .NET\"  - Jeremy Miller, Jimmy Bogart, etc. (Scott Bellware was part of this, loud mouth, bad guy, IMO) \n\n- JUnit (Kent Beck) - NUnit - MSTest (HORRIBLE (v1) and WORSE documentation)\n    - MSTest if Fine now. Good even. Don't sweat it.\n\n- Hibernate - NHibernate - Pretty darned good.\n    - Entity Framework. v1 - abomination against god and nature.\n\n\nScott Guthrie\n    - He coded up the first beta of ASP.NET MVC\n            - MVC - Model View Controller, a Small Talk separation of concerns pattern.\n              the same pattern that Ruby on Rails (the hawtness at the time) used.\n\n\n- They were going to for the first time include open source software (jQuery)\n   in the distribution.\n- For right now, ASp.NET mvc will be \"Shared Source\", but we will make it open source.\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "\"Alt .NET\"  - Jeremy Miller, Jimmy Bogart, etc. (Scott Bellware was part of this, loud mouth, bad guy, IMO) \n\n- JUnit (Kent Beck) - NUnit - MSTest (HORRIBLE (v1) and WORSE documentation)\n    - MSTest if Fine now. Good even. Don't sweat it.\n\n- Hibernate - NHibernate - Pretty darned good.\n    - Entity Framework. v1 - abomination against god and nature.\n\n\nScott Guthrie\n    - He coded up the first beta of ASP.NET MVC\n            - MVC - Model View Controller, a Small Talk separation of concerns pattern.\n              the same pattern that Ruby on Rails (the hawtness at the time) used.\n\n\n- They were going to for the first time include open source software (jQuery)\n   in the distribution.\n- For right now, ASp.NET mvc will be \"Shared Source\", but we will make it open source.\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
